&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meet or exceed area sales goals; manage promotional budgets and execute national sales strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and develop Regional Managers and Clinical Specialists, serving as the primary link between field teams and senior management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with Area Key Opinion Leaders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify market opportunities, share best practices, and proactively communicate strategies to cross-functional partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor pipeline of future enrollments and pull-through of current patients awaiting therapy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver accurate monthly and quarterly forecasts to senior leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate expert knowledge of market access and managed markets; ensure timely, compliant patient shipment processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee performance management, disciplinary processes, and recruiting, hiring, training, and retention for all area team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide frequent coaching and feedback to direct reports; foster a collaborative, supportive environment that drives retention and patient outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend commercial leadership meetings; address business issues and recommend solutions to improve productivity and operational efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate and communicate deep subject matter expertise across the disease space&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with all federal and state regulations, PhRMA guidelines, and Corcept policies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Skills, Qualifications and Technical Proficiencies:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to lead, inspire, and coach area and regional sales teams toward exceeding objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong leadership, strategic thinking, business planning, and analytical skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent

